notesStmt.note: Title for set from introduction to second work.

msContents.summary: Set of works on mathematics and astronomy copied together in what appears to be the same hand. The second work has a supercommentary copied in the margins. Several leaves of calculations and notations tipped or laid in; two tipped in pages have been foliated along with the leaves (f. 26, 33). Also includes one page in Ottoman Turkish (f.94v).
msContents.textLang: Arabic with one page in Ottoman Turkish

author.persName: Baghdādī, Jamāl al-Dīn ibn Maḥfūẓ, active 13th century?
Birjandī, ʻAbd al-ʻAlī ibn Muḥammad ibn Ḥusayn, active 16th century
برجندي، عبد العلي بن محمد بن حسين،

msItem.title: Margins: [Ḥāshiyat al-Birjandī ʻalá Sharḥ Qāḍīʹzādah al-Rūmī ʻalá al-Mulakhkhaṣ]
[Ḥāshiyah ʻalá Baḥth al-Shaʻīrāt fī Sharḥ al-Mulakhkhaṣ]

supportDesc.extent: 119 foliated leaves + 5 : 207 x 150 (160 x 85) mm, bound to 210 x 160 mm

layoutDesc.layout: 21-25 lines; some leaves with extensive marginalia on three sides.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Rubrications in red including terms, overlining, diagrams. Numerous geometrical diagrams throughout.

binding.p: Quarter covers of paper over pasteboard with faint, green design visible; brown leather spine; back cover partially detached; endbands in red and yellow.

origin.p: Copied in Turkey, parts of the manuscript are dated from Ṣafar 1081 AH (f. 86v) to Ramaḍān 1082 AH (f. 119v).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by George Arthur Plimpton (bookplate inside front cover).
